  "title": "The Highest Engagement Rate Posts From Pittsburgh Small Businesses",
  "subtitle": "Ranked by engagement as a percentage of follower count, not absolute likes. The punching-above-weight list.",
  "angle": "Pittsburgh's IG posts with the strongest reach relative to their account size. Small businesses can beat national chains here.",
  "intro": "The engagement rate list does not care how many followers you have. It cares what you do with them. That is the whole point of this ranking: we computed likes, comments, and weighted video plays as a percentage of each account's actual follower base, which means a tight-knit neighborhood coffee shop can absolutely outrank a regional chain with half a million followers. This quarter, they did.\n\nDelanie's Coffee in Shadyside topped the list at 39.29 percent, on a caption that was essentially just a honky tonk shoutout and a photographer credit. Spot of Coffee, working with a follower base under 3,000, placed second and fifth simultaneously, at 39.03 and 20.38 percent. Page's ice cream shop cracked the top three with a pickle split sundae announcement that hit 27.94 percent, which, for a six-figure follower account, is genuinely hard to do.\n\nThirty posts, seventeen businesses, a two-post-per-account cap to keep any single player from dominating the board. Issue 02 will track whether these same businesses can hold their efficiency advantage as their audiences grow, or whether size eventually wins after all.",
